Uses of Package
de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.custom

  • Packages that use de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.custom 
    Package Description
    de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.custom
    Provides custom enumerations and service handlers to support portlet classes
    de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.portlet
    Provides basic portlet classes common to all portlets
    de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.service
    Generated by Liferay: Contains service-builder interfaces
    de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.service.impl
    Provides service implementation classes for stubs generated by Liferay's service-builder
    de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.service.persistence
    (Partly) generated by Liferay: Contains service-builder utility classes

    Additionally provides finder classes with custom SQL queries.
    de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.socialize
    Provides classes for integration of social media services
  • Classes in de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.custom used by de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.custom 
    Class and Description
    E_CategoryType
    An enum describing data-lists available to forms
    E_ConfigCategory
    A config category bundles several E_ConfigKey together and is itself grouped by a parent E_ConfigDomain
    E_ConfigDomain
    A config domain bundles several E_ConfigCategory and should be used in the view to group those categories together
    E_ConfigKey
    An enum describing available configuration keys, their default value and (if available) their link/id to global portal settings
    E_ConfigType
    An enum describing input types of configuration settings, to allow dynamic forms for settings configuration
    E_OfferStatus
    An enum describing different offer status
    E_OfferType
    An enum describing the basic different types of offers TODO: Use dynamic data-lists instead
    E_OfferWorkType
    An enum describing the work-type of an offer TODO : Make configurable as data-list
    E_OrderType
    An enumeration that describes an ordering type on a database table column.
    E_OrgStatus
    An enum describing the current moderation state of an organisation
    E_Role
    An enum describing supported roles along with their default locations to redirect to after login.
    E_SocialMediaPlugins
    An enum describing supported social media plugins Uses bit-wise identifiers to address multiple plugins at once.
    E_SubscriptionStatus
    An enum describing status values available for subscriptions
    E_TableColumn
    An enum describing columns of tables, actually implemented for sorting
